{"article_id":"2Gm2D8EgZneZXbAb","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"\" One thing","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"I ' ve learned in politics","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"-","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"there really is never an oversaturation point for a righteous message , \"","depth":3},{"id":4,"text":"said Sen. Chris Murphy","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"( D-Conn. ) ,","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"who added","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"that Democratic demands are in line with public polling .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"\" It makes sense to repeat it over and over and over again . \"","depth":3},{"id":9,"text":"Democrats will need at least four Republicans to join their calls for witnesses and documents ;","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"a few obvious targets are Sen. Susan Collins","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"( R-Maine ) ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Mitt Romney","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"( R-Utah )","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"and Lisa Murkowski","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"( R-Alaska ) .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"But","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"while Collins has said","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"she is likely to support bringing in witnesses","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"after she hears opening arguments from both sides ,","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"she ' s also publicly complained about Schumer ' s heavy-handed approach .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"When asked about the effectiveness of Schumer ' s media appearances ,","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"Annie Clark , a spokeswoman for Collins , said","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"the Maine Republican \" has been busy working","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"and hasn ' t had time","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"to watch much TV . \"","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Schumer ' s media approach to the Senate impeachment trial is diametrically opposed to that of Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"( R-Ky. )","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"who hasn ' t held a news conference since the start of the trial","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"and has saved his remarks for the Senate chamber .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"\" Leader McConnell ' s results on the floor speak for themselves , \"","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"said Doug Andres , a spokesman for McConnell ,","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"referencing the Senate ' s passage early Wednesday morning of the GOP leader ' s resolution","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"setting the contours of the impeachment trial .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"Despite Schumer ' s best efforts ,","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"a series of votes","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"he forced well into the early hours of Wednesday morning","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"to secure witnesses and documents","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"failed , nearly entirely along party lines .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"Schumer did keep his caucus together ,","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"with moderate Sens . Joe Manchin of West Virginia and Kyrsten Sinema of Arizona joining the rest of the Democratic senators on the procedural votes .","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"Because McConnell and Schumer were unable to reach an agreement on timing for the votes ,","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"senators were stuck in the chamber until 1 a.m .","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"\" Who couldn ' t have been a little annoyed by that ? \"","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"asked Sen. Mike Braun of Indiana .","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"\" It set the tone for what our staying power is . \"","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"\" He predictably overstays his welcome and his effectiveness , \"","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"added Sen. Kevin Cramer of North Dakota .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"\" He goes from having momentum","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"to hitting the bottom pretty fast","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"and I think","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"he can not resist overplaying [ his ] hand . \"","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Prior to the start of the Senate impeachment trial Wednesday , GOP Sens . Lindsey Graham of South Carolina , Steve Daines of Montana and Braun held a news conference of their own","depth":4},{"id":53,"text":"to defend the president","depth":5},{"id":54,"text":"and chastise Democrats .","depth":5},{"id":55,"text":"But some Trump allies aren ' t arguing with Schumer ' s strategy .","depth":5},{"id":56,"text":"Rep. Mark Meadows","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"( R-N.C. ) ,","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"a fierce Trump defender , acknowledged","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"that the Democratic leader was helping his party ' s cause","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"by putting himself out there ,","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"adding","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"that he \" can ' t be critical of the other side","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"if I think","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"it ' s a good idea for our side . \"","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"Democrats are eager to deliver some countermessaging to Trump ,","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"who can easily seize the public ' s attention with his Twitter megaphone .","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"And Schumer has encouraged his members at party lunches to flood the airwaves in a range of media outlets ,","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"according to a source familiar with the strategy .","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"His own caucus also views Schumer as its lead messenger .","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"\" I think","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"there has to be an alternative","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"given everything","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"that we see","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"coming from the other side , \"","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"said Sen. Doug Jones","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"( D-Ala. ) ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"the most vulnerable Democrat up for reelection .","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"\" There has to be some other voice out there .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"He doesn ' t speak for everybody ,","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"he doesn ' t always speak for me ,","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"but I think","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"there has to be some alternative","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"[ to Trump ] . \"","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":167,"left":92,"right":166,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":92,"left":87,"right":91,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":87,"left":86,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":86,"left":85,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":85,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":91,"left":90,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":90,"left":88,"right":89,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":88,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":89,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":166,"left":134,"right":165,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":134,"left":116,"right":133,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":108,"right":115,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":108,"left":9,"right":107,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":97,"right":106,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":97,"left":93,"right":96,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":93,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":94,"right":95,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":94,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":101,"right":105,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":100,"right":20,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":100,"left":16,"right":99,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":99,"left":17,"right":98,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":98,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":102,"right":